Text: RE Tradesbark Cc legal EES also has an agreement with TradeSpark Let me know if you need more information Will From Mark nronXgate on AM To Joanne nronXgate cc Jeffrey T nronXGate Mark nronXgate William ES Subject RE Tradesbark Joanne I believe Pat was inquiring as to TradeSpark We have agreements with ENA and EPMI that were signed earlier this year I believe we also have one with EES but this was negotiated by Will F We would have to check with him about the status Let me know what needs to be done on this matter Mark Original Message From Rozycki Joanne Sent Monday November AM To Greenberg Mark Cc Griffin Vanessa Subject Tradesbark Pat Kokes a Contract Administrator with Dynegy at called this morning requesting info on Electronic Trading Agreements with Tradesbark for Enron Capital Enron Energy Services Enron Global Mktg Enron Power Mktg Jeff Hodge said you would probably be the one to refer this to If possible please give Mr Kokes a call back today Thanks Joanne Rozycki Senior Administrative Assistant Enron North America Corp Smith Street EBD Houston TX Phone Fax Email

RE lunchI am open that week How about Tuesday From Richard B nronXgate on AM To William ES cc Subject RE lunch I am going to Las Vegas for Thanksgiving but am available any day but Monday next week Let me know your schedule Original Message From Frederking William Sent Friday November PM To Sanders Richard B Subject lunch Are you available for lunch next week Will

Conectiv Power Delivery New Jersey Third Party Supplier Agreement Cc Carol Jim Keller suggested that I send the attached memo to you EES is attempting to become licensed to provide competitive energy supply to New Jersey customers Conectiv has stated that they are unable to accept modifications to the Supplier Agreement The purpose of the attached memo is to provide a summary of the primary provisions we attempted to amend so that a determination may be made as to whether EES should execute the Supplier Agreement Please call me at x if you have any questions or comments Thanks Will

Baltimore Gas Electric Cc Jim I am in the process of reviewing many of EES utility agreements for the northeast The Application to Supply Gas under Schedule DSG with BGE signed requires EES to notify BGE of any deterioration in its creditworthiness or any assignment made for the benefit of creditors within the month such deterioration or assignment occurs I will let you know if I find anything else of note Give me a call if you have any questions Will
